per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.469 g","calories":"467 kJ \/ 111 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, 2 ramekins, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can use either Swiss brown mushrooms or field mushrooms in this recipe.","Pepperleaf has the warm heat of black pepper, combined with a \"bushy\", eucalyptus flavour. You can find it online or in specialty spice stores. Otherwise, you can replace the pepperleaf with 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper.","Serve with crackers or slices of baguette toasted with extra virgin olive oil. Or try spreading over grilled steak or chicken."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","2h 50m","10 portions"]}